President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Iowa due to severe winter storms that occurred between January 19-26, 2010. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available to the state, eligible local governments, and certain nonprofit organizations for emergency work, facility repairs, and hazard mitigation measures. Thomas A. Hall has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area, and additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.